1. Initialize dp array with all elements set to Integer.MAX_VALUE.
2. Iterate through the array and for each element, check if it is less than or equal to the remaining sum after subtracting the current element from the total sum.
3. If the element is valid, update the dp array by taking the minimum of the current dp value and the dp value of the subset without the current element plus 1.
4. Return the value at index k in the dp array, which represents the number of ways to partition the array into k subsets with equal sums.
5. Calculate the sum of the input array using a for-each loop and return the result.

The time complexity is O(n * k) because we iterate through the array and for each element, we iterate through all subsets of size k. The space complexity is O(k) because we use a k-sized array to store the dp values. The energy implications are low because the problem does not involve any energy-consuming operations.

